get.description:
PREVIEW - This Web API retrieves the corresponding systems along with registration details for a systemtype.
            Needs a valid system type and a well-formatted query as required parameters to be executed.
                Optional parameters: operationName, namedQuery.
                Cannot send mutations within the query.
                If data is present within the Json returned then errors will be empty.
                By default query returns max 50 records. This limitation can be overridden by passing 'first' argument in the Query.
             Return shape:
             {
               "data":{
                   "systemRegistryDetails": {
                        "systemType": "type1",
                        "systems": [
                        {
                          "systemId": "system1",
                          "systemGuid": "516e5e80-1eb5-41da-b494-420a4cd0374a",
                          "details": "systemmetadata",
                          "provisioningStatus": "Provisioned"
                        },
                       {
                         "systemId": "system3",
                         "systemGuid": "84b30576-3c21-4a70-9b92-fd1bd6b13e79",
                         "details": "systemmetadata",
                         "provisioningStatus": "Provisioned"
                       }]         
                    }
                },
                "errors": [
                 {
                   "locations": [
                   {
                     "line": 1,
                     "column": 5
                   }],
                   "message": "errorMessage"
                 }]
                }
<p><b>Authorization:</b>SystemTypeActivity-SearchSystemRegistry</p>
<p><b>Action:</b>SystemRegistryQuery</p>

parameters.description:
A GraphQL to be executed
             Query example:
             query namedQuery{
                systemRegistryDetails(systemType: "type1" )
                {
                    systemType
                    systems(provisioningStatus: "Provisioned" first: 2)
                    {
                        systemId
                        systemGuid
                        details
                        provisioningStatus
                    }
                }
            }

